net.kuujo.copycat.raft.log

Class Entry<T extends Entry<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.kuujo.copycat.raft.log.Entry<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, CopycatSerializable, ReferenceCounted<Entry>

    public abstract class Entry<T extends Entry<T>>
extends Object
implements ReferenceCounted<Entry>, CopycatSerializable
    Log entry.

    The Entry represents a single record in a Copycat Log. Each entry is stored at a unique index in the log. Indexes are applied to entries once written to a log.

    Custom entry implementations should implement serialization and deserialization logic via CopycatSerializable.writeObject(net.kuujo.copycat.io.BufferOutput, net.kuujo.copycat.io.serializer.Serializer) and CopycatSerializable.readObject(net.kuujo.copycat.io.BufferInput, net.kuujo.copycat.io.serializer.Serializer). respectively.

    Author:
    Jordan Halterman
